text: Incase you dont succeed, it is better to lose capital invested from you than borrowed capital. Alot of people fail to realize this, hence when the business flops,  they're more engrossed on how to payback the borrowed capital.Than dealing with flop of the business.

author: Ohia Mirian Adanna
text: Never start up a business  with a borrowed capital. Let the capital be yours only and never invest all your capital into the proposed business. Rather start SMALL, if you succeed then you can invest more and expand. That way the risk is minimized  to just you losing your capital
